records.addlTxt:
Defendant Marcos V Alvarez in court with attorney Julius Andriusis.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions:  
*  Perform 25 hours of community service;
*  Possess no firearms;
*  Write a letter of apology to Officer Thomas Slowinski - MPD;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.

Upon successful completion of conditions of a probation, probation may be terminated early.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
